  "content": {
    "bodyModel": {
      "paragraphs": [
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_0",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f6ff",
          "text": "Finding Hope Beyond Your Own Lifetime",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "H3"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_1",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3c14",
          "text": "Living in a world of planetary crisis requires that we take the long view.",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*UXaJnrSs2HjwUf1rQB7zXQ.png",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_2",
          "href": null,
          "name": "b1a0",
          "text": "The future of humanity will be determined by those who take the long view. We are living through a planetary crisis right now, the consequences of which are literally global in proportions. It helps to remember an astounding fact — that once life took hold on the fledgling Earth 3.8 billion years ago, there has never been a time since that life didn’t exist. This is because living things are organically predisposed for taking the long view.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 115,
              "href": "https://extranewsfeed.com/living-through-the-death-of-capitalism-94629d79f036#.rwkd01n3r",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 99,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 301,
              "href": "http://www.bbc.co.uk/nature/history_of_the_earth",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 280,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_3",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1cf2",
          "text": "An unbroken chain of mothers and daughters spans the geologic ages between then and now. As we watch the 11,000 year stable period of planetary climate (called the Holocene) come to an end — thanks to the human activities that created global warming — it is vital that we also take the long view.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 172,
              "href": "http://www.ucmp.berkeley.edu/quaternary/holocene.php",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 163,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 250,
              "href": "https://extranewsfeed.com/the-climate-doomsday-is-already-here-556a0763c11d#.dr7oz8645",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 227,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_4",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f22e",
          "text": "I say this as a man whose wife just gave birth to our first child three weeks ago. We held in our arms a new life, knowing full well that the Earth is in crisis with acidifying oceans, topsoil losses, the buildup of greenhouse gases, and a mass extinction event directly and indirectly caused by human land use practices. According to the Stockholm Resilience Institute, four of the nine “planetary boundaries” that define a safe operation space for the global economy have already been crossed. We are now in overshoot-and-collapse as a civilization.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 494,
              "href": "https://scripps.ucsd.edu/news/earth-has-crossed-several-planetary-boundaries-thresholds-human-induced-environmental-changes",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 470,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 532,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 510,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_5",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7fb1",
          "text": "Our daughter was born within days of a lunatic narcissist taking office in the United States. She will grow up in the most economically unequal world our species has ever known (current estimates are that fewer than 62 people have the same aggregate wealth as 3.7 billion). This is a world where financial collapse is imminent, oil production has globally peaked, civil unrest is rampant on every continent where humans live, and the future is profoundly uncertain.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 225,
              "href": "https://www.oxfam.org/en/pressroom/pressreleases/2016-01-18/62-people-own-same-half-world-reveals-oxfam-davos-report",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 205,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "7127",
          "text": "One does not look into the eyes of a newborn in times such as these and take a short view… only the distant horizon will do.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 124,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ec5b",
          "text": "This is what we are doing as we go through the daily routines of nursing and changing diapers. Not content to be swept away by social media hype about the latest insanity of a corrupt political system, we focus our hearts on a lifetime of struggle that our child will know as she grows up in the midst of a Great Transition for Humanity — we are now in the crucible of change and will soon have made the collective decision to either grow up as planetary stewards or go the way of the Dodo by remaining stuck in cultural adolescence.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1b6d",
          "text": "This choice will not be made by those who take the short view. It will be made by those who either chose the long view or merely rode the waves of disruption without clear moral intent for what the future might hold. Every single person alive right now is complicit in the downfall of our biosphere. Therefore every single person alive right now is responsible for moving their own life sphere away from extractive economic hoarding — the global default for parasitic capitalism — and toward full-on regenerative design.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 432,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/the-global-architecture-of-wealth-extraction-4c0a6b954a14#.ncappewxd",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 404,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c692",
          "text": "Whether we call this culture design, culture hacking, or the way of intentional living, it will still be the emergent outcome of our collective intelligence (or our collective stupidity) that determines the long-term fate of our species.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 35,
              "href": "https://medium.com/age-of-awareness/culture-design-labs-evolving-the-future-94455c446ff5#.yu94211go",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 21,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 86,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@joe_brewer/toward-a-science-of-intentional-change-4ca992ebd9b5#.4lti5ea2u",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 61,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 156,
              "href": "https://medium.com/emergent-future/the-connective-intelligence-of-life-41f4b31a3ef#.nmsgzyqia",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 133,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4c4a",
          "text": "I, for one, am taking the long view.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d92301bbde55_11",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8724",
          "text": "Onward, fellow humans.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
